Anonymous Sun 20 Aug 2023 16:16:18 No.58936197 Report
Quoted By: >>58936422
>>58934276
I'll take a swing.

Mustilids do better with beady eyes (natural) or wide but narrow (consider, Mienshao) where the toon size comes from the eyelids but maintain a sleek appearance. Big wide round like here doesn't signal either the species or the stereotype of something long and slinky.

Mouth seems kinda rubbery. The teeth follow the lips instead of the jawbone to where it joins the skull. Upper teeth look more snake than mammal fang and underline the upper/lower jaw mismatch.

Right arm posture is odd. I think it's that the forearm suggests palm forward, wrist kinked hard right (which hurts my carpal tunnel to try). Let the passport be tilted in a bit more and angled a little inward. The way you have it better presents the side-by-side intent, but removes spatial hints that in a bare lineart are vital. Treat them like tangents. If this were shaded/colored it would probably look less awkward.

I like that the tail seems to come out of the spine rather than one side of the hip (so many do weird crap like that) but I think it's kinked up too high. I'd have it lowered to better agree with the rest of the spine.
